   "source": [
    "# N-Sufficiency Calibration Model (Colab)\n",
    "\n",
    "Calibrates the satellite N-sufficiency score (0–100 proxy from CIre / NDRE)\n",
    "against measured leaf/soil N from field trials.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Pipeline\n",
    "1. Pull diagnostics cache + photo submissions from Supabase.\n",
    "2. Extract per-cell CIre, NDRE, GNDVI, NDMI, growth stage from EE (same bands as `diagnostics` edge function).\n",
    "3. Join with `farmer_photo_submissions.soil_test_result` where `nitrogen_kg_ha` is present.\n",
    "4. Train a Ridge regression: spectral features → N kg/ha.\n",
    "5. Export `n_calibration.json` to Google Drive → drop into the edge function.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Schema contract\n",
    "The exported JSON (`NCalibrationJSON`) is loaded by `calculateNitrogenSufficiency()` in\n",
    "`supabase/functions/diagnostics/index.ts`. Format:\n",
    "```json\n",
    "{\n",
    "  \"version\": \"ridge-v1\",\n",
    "  \"features\": [\"cire\", \"ndre\", \"gndvi\", \"ndmi\"],\n",
    "  \"intercept\": 42.3,\n",
    "  \"coef\": { \"cire\": 8.1, \"ndre\": 35.2, \"gndvi\": 18.6, \"ndmi\": 5.4 },\n",
    "  \"stage_bias\": {\n",
    "    \"pre_emergence\": 0,\n",
    "    \"tillering\": 0,\n",
    "    \"booting\": -5,\n",
    "    \"heading\": -8,\n",
    "    \"ripening\": -12\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"r2_cv\": 0.71,\n",
    "  \"n_samples\": 134,\n",
    "  \"trained_date\": \"2026-06-23\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "```\n",
    "Until this file is trained and deployed, the edge function uses the CIre/NDRE\n",
    "weighted-score formula (v4-cire). This notebook does NOT break anything — it\n",
    "only produces an optional calibration artefact.\n",
    "\n",
    "## When to run\n",
    "Once ≥50 matched (spectral, lab-N) samples are in the DB. Re-run seasonally.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-setup",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Setup ---\n",
    "!pip -q install earthengine-api supabase requests pandas scikit-learn\n",
    "import ee, requests, json, datetime as dt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import RidgeCV\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from supabase import create_client\n",
    "\n",
    "# GEE auth — service account or interactive\n",
    "ee.Authenticate()\n",
    "ee.Initialize(project='YOUR_GEE_PROJECT_ID')\n",
    "\n",
    "SUPABASE_URL = 'https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co'\n",
    "SUPABASE_KEY = 'YOUR_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY'\n",
    "sb = create_client(SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_KEY)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-ee-features",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- EE spectral features (MUST match diagnostics/index.ts calculateSpectralFeatures) ---\n",
    "S2_BANDS  = ['B2','B3','B4','B5','B8','B11','B12']\n",
    "S2_ALIAS  = ['blue','green','red','rededge','nir','swir1','swir2']\n",
    "\n",
    "def s2_composite(geom, start_date, end_date):\n",
    "    col = (\n",
    "        ee.ImageCollection('COPERNICUS/S2_SR_HARMONIZED')\n",
    "        .filterBounds(geom)\n",
    "        .filterDate(start_date, end_date)\n",
    "        .filter(ee.Filter.lt('CLOUDY_PIXEL_PERCENTAGE', 60))\n",
    "        .map(lambda im: im.select(S2_BANDS, S2_ALIAS).multiply(0.0001).clamp(0, 1))\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return col.median().clip(geom)\n",
    "\n",
    "def spectral_features(geom, start_date, end_date):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Returns dict of CIre, NDRE, GNDVI, NDMI for the geometry/date window.\"\"\"\n",
    "    c = s2_composite(geom, start_date, end_date)\n",
    "    nir     = c.select('nir')\n",
    "    green   = c.select('green')\n",
    "    rededge = c.select('rededge')\n",
    "    swir1   = c.select('swir1')\n",
    "\n",
    "    cire  = nir.divide(rededge.max(ee.Image(0.001))).subtract(1).clamp(0, 15).rename('cire')\n",
    "    ndre  = nir.subtract(rededge).divide(nir.add(rededge).max(ee.Image(0.001))).clamp(0, 1).rename('ndre')\n",
    "    gndvi = nir.subtract(green).divide(nir.add(green)).clamp(-1, 1).rename('gndvi')\n",
    "    ndmi  = nir.subtract(swir1).divide(nir.add(swir1)).clamp(-1, 1).rename('ndmi')\n",
    "\n",
    "    stack = cire.addBands([ndre, gndvi, ndmi])\n",
    "    vals = stack.reduceRegion(\n",
    "        reducer=ee.Reducer.mean(),\n",
    "        geometry=geom,\n",
    "        scale=10,\n",
    "        maxPixels=1e9,\n",
    "        bestEffort=True\n",
    "    ).getInfo()\n",
    "    return vals  # {cire, ndre, gndvi, ndmi}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-load-labels",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Pull labeled samples from Supabase ---\n",
    "# Source 1: photo submissions with soil_test_result.nitrogen_kg_ha\n",
    "subs = (\n",
    "    sb.table('farmer_photo_submissions')\n",
    "    .select('farm_id, taken_lat, taken_lng, crop, growth_stage, soil_test_result, submitted_at')\n",
    "    .not_.is_('soil_test_result', 'null')\n",
    "    .execute().data\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter to rows with lab N measurement\n",
    "labeled = []\n",
    "for s in subs:\n",
    "    lab = s.get('soil_test_result') or {}\n",
    "    n_kgha = lab.get('nitrogen_kg_ha')\n",
    "    if n_kgha is None:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    lat = s.get('taken_lat')\n",
    "    lng = s.get('taken_lng')\n",
    "    if lat is None or lng is None:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    labeled.append({\n",
    "        'lat': lat, 'lng': lng,\n",
    "        'n_kgha': float(n_kgha),\n",
    "        'growth_stage': s.get('growth_stage', 'tillering'),\n",
    "        'date': (s.get('submitted_at') or dt.date.today().isoformat())[:10],\n",
    "        'farm_id': s.get('farm_id'),\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'{len(labeled)} samples with lab N data')\n",
    "# Need ≥50 to train. If fewer, skip to the \"what to collect\" section below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-extract-features",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Extract EE spectral features for each labeled sample ---\n",
    "rows = []\n",
    "for i, s in enumerate(labeled):\n",
    "    print(f'[{i+1}/{len(labeled)}] {s[\"farm_id\"]} {s[\"date\"]}')\n",
    "    end   = s['date']\n",
    "    start = (dt.date.fromisoformat(end) - dt.timedelta(days=21)).isoformat()\n",
    "    pt    = ee.Geometry.Point([s['lng'], s['lat']]).buffer(50)  # ~50m radius\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        feats = spectral_features(pt, start, end)\n",
    "        if feats.get('cire') is None:\n",
    "            print(f'  -> no S2 imagery, skipping')\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        row = {**feats, 'n_kgha': s['n_kgha'], 'growth_stage': s['growth_stage']}\n",
    "        rows.append(row)\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f'  -> EE error: {e}')\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n",
    "print(f'\\n{len(df)} samples with both EE features and lab N')\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-train",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Train Ridge regression ---\n",
    "FEATURE_COLS = ['cire', 'ndre', 'gndvi', 'ndmi']\n",
    "\n",
    "if len(df) < 50:\n",
    "    print(f'Only {len(df)} samples — need ≥50. Use the current CIre/NDRE weighted-score formula.')\n",
    "    print('Collect soil-test reports via the app and re-run this notebook when data grows.')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    X = df[FEATURE_COLS].fillna(0).values\n",
    "    y = df['n_kgha'].values\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Stage dummies for bias adjustment (optional — add if R² improves)\n",
    "    # stage_map = {'pre_emergence':0,'tillering':1,'booting':2,'heading':3,'ripening':4}\n",
    "    # X = np.hstack([X, df['growth_stage'].map(stage_map).fillna(1).values.reshape(-1,1)])\n",
    "\n",
    "    scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "    Xs = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "\n",
    "    model = RidgeCV(alphas=[0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100], cv=5)\n",
    "    model.fit(Xs, y)\n",
    "\n",
    "    scores = cross_val_score(model, Xs, y, cv=5, scoring='r2')\n",
    "    print(f'Ridge alpha={model.alpha_:.3f}  CV R²={scores.mean():.3f} ± {scores.std():.3f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Unscale coefficients back to raw feature space\n",
    "    raw_coef = model.coef_ / scaler.scale_\n",
    "    raw_intercept = model.intercept_ - (scaler.mean_ / scaler.scale_ @ model.coef_)\n",
    "\n",
    "    coef_dict = {col: float(raw_coef[i]) for i, col in enumerate(FEATURE_COLS)}\n",
    "    print('Coefficients (raw feature space):'); print(coef_dict)\n",
    "    print(f'Intercept: {raw_intercept:.3f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-export",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Export calibration JSON ---\n",
    "# Only run this cell if the model trained successfully above.\n",
    "\n",
    "calibration = {\n",
    "    'version': 'ridge-v1',\n",
    "    'features': FEATURE_COLS,\n",
    "    'intercept': float(raw_intercept),\n",
    "    'coef': coef_dict,\n",
    "    # Stage bias (kg/ha adjustment relative to tillering baseline):\n",
    "    # Fill these in from domain knowledge or a per-stage regression.\n",
    "    'stage_bias': {\n",
    "        'pre_emergence': 0,\n",
    "        'tillering': 0,\n",
    "        'booting': -5,\n",
    "        'heading': -8,\n",
    "        'ripening': -12\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'r2_cv': float(scores.mean()),\n",
    "    'n_samples': int(len(df)),\n",
    "    'trained_date': dt.date.today().isoformat(),\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Write locally\n",
    "out_local = f'n_calibration_{dt.date.today().isoformat()}.json'\n",
    "with open(out_local, 'w') as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(calibration, f, indent=2)\n",
    "print('Wrote', out_local)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Export to Google Drive (optional)\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    from google.colab import drive\n",
    "    drive.mount('/content/drive')\n",
    "    drive_path = f'/content/drive/MyDrive/wrkFarm/n_calibration_{dt.date.today().isoformat()}.json'\n",
    "    with open(drive_path, 'w') as f:\n",
    "        json.dump(calibration, f, indent=2)\n",
    "    print('Wrote to Drive:', drive_path)\n",
    "except Exception:\n",
    "    print('Not in Colab — skipping Drive export')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nNext step: add this JSON to GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_JSON or a Supabase secret')\n",
    "print('and load it in calculateNitrogenSufficiency() in diagnostics/index.ts')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-collection",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## What to collect to train this model\n",
    "\n",
    "The model needs matched (spectral, lab-N) pairs. Fastest path:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Source | How |\n",
    "|--------|-----|\n",
    "| Soil tests | Enter `nitrogen_kg_ha` in `farmer_photo_submissions.soil_test_result` via the app photo-submit flow when a farmer has a lab report |\n",
    "| ICAR trial data | Download AICRIP (All India Coordinated Rice Improvement Programme) yield trials — they include leaf N at each growth stage |\n",
    "| KVK demonstrations | Coordinate with nearest KVK to share soil-health card data against farm GPS |\n",
    "\n",
    "Target: **100+ samples** across at least 3 growth stages and 2 soil types before training.\n",
    "Re-run this notebook each kharif/rabi season and redeploy `n_calibration.json`.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Edge function integration hook\n",
    "\n",
    "Once `n_calibration.json` is ready, add this to `calculateNitrogenSufficiency()` in\n",
    "`supabase/functions/diagnostics/index.ts`:\n",
    "\n",
    "```typescript\n",
    "// When N_CALIBRATION_JSON env var is set, use calibrated kg/ha instead of 0–100 proxy\n",
    "const cal = Deno.env.get('N_CALIBRATION_JSON');\n",
    "if (cal) {\n",
    "  const { intercept, coef, stage_bias } = JSON.parse(cal);\n",
    "  const rawN = intercept\n",
    "    + coef.cire  * cireVal\n",
    "    + coef.ndre  * ndreVal\n",
    "    + coef.gndvi * gndviVal\n",
    "    + coef.ndmi  * ndmiVal\n",
    "    + (stage_bias[currentStage] ?? 0);\n",
    "  // Map kg/ha to 0–100: 0 kg/ha → 0, sufficiency threshold (e.g. 120 kg/ha) → 100\n",
    "  return ee.Image.constant(Math.max(0, Math.min(100, rawN / 1.2)));\n",
    "}\n",
    "// Fallback: existing CIre/NDRE weighted score\n",
    "```\n"
   ]
  }
 ]
